Hello,

I had a look into this ticket https://github.com/mozilla/django-csp/issues/105, but could not find any answer to solve my issue.
I wanted to add csp_update to the password reset form in django, but it does not work for me in order to add recaptcha only there.
If i set the variables globally (in setting.py), it works perfectly.
None of the CSP variables are taken into account.

Here is the code of my view : 
```python
from csp.decorators import csp_update, csp
from django.contrib.auth.views import PasswordResetView
from django.utils.decorators import method_decorator


class MyPasswordResetView(PasswordResetView):

    @method_decorator(csp(DEFAULT_SRC="www.google.com"))
    @method_decorator(csp_update(SCRIPT_SRC="'unsafe-inline'"))
    @method_decorator(csp_update(SCRIPT_SRC="www.gstatic.com"))
    @method_decorator(csp_update(SCRIPT_SRC="google.com"))
    def dispatch(self, *args, **kwargs):
        return super().dispatch(*args, **kwargs)
```

Do you have any clue on the issue ?
Thx,
Jérémie

